Description:
Quality home in good location
This three bedroom brick veneer home is in a fantastic location comprising open plan living. The kitchen offers an excellent amount of bench space with cooktop, wall oven and dishwasher. It overlooks a generous sized lounge and separate meals and is heated and cooled by a reverse cycle split system. All three bedrooms offer built in robes and ceiling fans, with the master having an reverse cycle split system. The three way bathroom has bath and shower with separate vanity area and separate toilet, making it ideal for families. Externally there is a double carport with roller door and outdoor entertaining area, but this area could easily accommodate up to four vehicles. There is also a colorbond shed, garden shed and good sized rear yard. This home would make an ideal investment property or first family home and will not disappoint.

Comfortable family home on 1300 square metre (approx.) block in quiet court. The home features open plan living with renovated kitchen, lounge with gas heater and separate dining area. Excellent presentation inside and out. A huge block, ideal for the family, or ripe for subdivision (STCA).

Description:
Classic Victorian Style Home
This hundred year old Victorian style home set on a corner block is more then meets the eye
Roselea cottage is fully renovated to its period.
Roselea cottage features twelve foot pressed tin ceilings, ceiling roses throughout with brass light fittings and switches
Three bedroom and one study also features ducted gas heating, evaporative cooling, electric stove and cook top and gas hot water system
This property is set on a quarter acre block and is in walking distance to town centre
The back yard features a large eleven meter by seven meter salt water solar heated pool and spa
It features an entertaining area with a built in fire pit
There is side entrance for caravan, trailer parking and a three meter by 3 meter garden shed
This property is a must to see

Description:
Location, Location, Location
Perfectly positioned only a stones throw from the bushland along the Murray River and along the much sought after Bisogni Drive, this 3 bedroom plus study home is not going to be on the market all that long! Everything about this perfectly presented home is big! The stunning timber kitchen with its stone benchtops has the most cupboards and benchspace in any home on the market at the moment. With all the usual mod cons such as electric wall oven, ceramic cooktop and dishwasher this kitchen also has most of the cupboards fitted with drawers to maximise the use of storage. This home has potentially three living spaces but at the very least offers two generous sized spaces. The master bedroom is positioned at the front of the home and comprises large WIR and Ensuite with double sized shower. The other bedrooms are located adjacent the family bathroom and laundry. Externally this home has an outdoor entertaining area and double garage with direct access into the home. For the caravan, boat or any other large toy, the driveway offers a parking bay area for those too! If you think this home might be for you, call now for an inspection.
